			<div n="1"><p><supplied reason="subaudible"><quote type="basetext" xml:lang="san-Latn" source="MDhŚ08.001">
				<lg met="anuṣṭubh">
				<l>vyavahārān didr̥kṣus tu brāhmaṇaiḥ saha pārthivaḥ</l>
				<l>mantrajñair mantribhiś caiva vinītaḥ praviśet sabhām ॥</l>
				</lg></quote></supplied></p>
<p>kunaṅ hulaha saṅ prabhu, uniṅānira taṅ vyavahāranikaṅ rāt,
harovaṅa ta sira brāhmaṇa vihikan maṅaji,
lavan <app><lem type="emn">mantri vruh</lem><rdg wit="#L">mantri riṁ vruḥ</rdg><rdg wit="#K">mantri, vruḥ</rdg></app>
<app><lem wit="#L">mavivekā</lem><rdg wit="#K">mavikvekā</rdg></app>,
sulakṣaṇaha ta sira tumamaha riṅ sabhā.</p></div>
<!--	L: [01-04] haliṅgiha pagəha ta sira riṁ sabha:, taṅanira tṅən hatah ulahaknira, hayva:tu[01-05]duḥtuduḥ kiva:,
bhūṣa:ṇa pahyasniṁ vvaṁ sugiḥla:taḥ lvirranira,
Iṅətiṅətəni[01-06]ra:taḥ yogya:yogyani karyyanikaṁ mavyava:hara kaliḥ ||
	K: haliṅgiḥ pagəha: ta sira riṁ śabha:, taṅanira tṅən hata[SH]h ula:knira, hayva tuduḥtuduḥ kiva:,
bhuṣa:ṇa payasniṁ vvaṁ śūśila:taḥ lviranira, Iṅətiṅətənira:taḥ hogya:[1v3]yogyaniṁ ka:ryyanikaṁ mavya:vara kaliḥ ||
-->
<div n="2"><p><supplied reason="subaudible"><quote type="basetext" xml:lang="san-Latn" source="MDhŚ08.002">
	<lg met="anuṣṭubh">
	<l>tatrāsīnaḥ sthito vāpi pāṇim udyamya dakṣiṇam |</l>
	<l>vinītaveṣābharaṇaḥ paśyet kāryāṇi kāryiṇām</l>
</lg></quote></supplied></p>
<p><app><lem type="norm">haliṅgihāpagəha</lem><rdg wit="#L">haliṅgih apagəha</rdg><rdg wit="#K">haliṅgiḥ pagəha:</rdg></app> ta sira riṅ sabhā, taṅanira tṅən hatah <app><lem wit="#L">ulahaknira</lem><rdg wit="#K">ula:knira</rdg></app>,
<app><lem wit="#L">hayvātuduh-tuduh</lem><rdg wit="#K">hayva tuduḥtuduḥ</rdg></app>*<!-- atuduh-tuduh is not in OJED --> kiva,
bhūṣaṇa-pahyasniṅ vvaṅ suśīlātah lviranira,
iṅət-iṅətənirātah yogyāyogyani kāryanikaṅ mavyavahāra kalih.</p>
</div>
<!--
L: sarī maśiha sira:n∙ ṅiṅətiṅəta makasa:danaṁ varavaraḥ saṁ hyaṁṅ a:gama [01-08] manava:vī,
		mvaṁ sa:kinapagəhaknikaṁ sapañjiṁ deśanya, sadaṅayan· sajamu[01-09]s∙ vuṅkal∙, savurava:n∙, sakanuruhan∙,
		An∙ hana kapaR̥kanya deni[01-10]ṅa:gama, ya hika: deśadr̥ṣṭa ṅaranya,
		hankan deśa sasiki śva:deśanikaṁ [01-11] vyava:hara, Aṣṭadaṣasu margge, Irika: stha:naniṁ vyava:hara vva:luvlas∙, kv[01-12]eḥnya, salviraniṁ vicaraniṁ vyava:hara,
		hana tinmunya ṅka:na salaḥ siki, pa[01-13]ḍa: madudva:dudva:n∙ viṣayanya ||
K: sarī masiha: siran∙ ṅiṅətiṅəta makasḍanaṁ varaḥvaraḥ [SH] saṅ hyaṁṅ a:gamma: manava:di,
	mvaṁ sakinapagəhaknikaṁ sapañjiṁ deṣanya, deṣa ṅaranya:, sadaṅayan sajamus∙ vuṅkal∙ [1v4], savuravan∙, sakanuruvan∙,
	An∙ hana: kapaR̥kanya denīṁ hagamma:, ya hika: deṣadṛṣṭa: ṅaranya: [SH]
	hankan deṣa sasiki śvadeṣanikaṁ vya:vahara, haṣṭa:deṣa:su ma:rgge, hirika ṣṭa:naniṁ vyavahara valuvlas∙ — [2r1] kveḥnya, salvir<aniṅ vicaran>iṅ vyavahara,
	 hana tinmunya ṅkana: salaḥ siki, pa<ḍa: ma>dudvadudvan∙ viṣayanya ||
-->
<div n="3"><p><supplied reason="subaudible"><quote type="basetext" xml:lang="san-Latn" source="MDhŚ08.003">
<lg met="anuṣṭubh">
	<l>pratyahaṁ deśadr̥ṣṭaiś ca śāstradr̥ṣṭaiś ca hetubhiḥ |</l>
	<l>aṣṭādaśasu mārgeṣu nibaddhāni pr̥thak pr̥thak ||</l>
	</lg>
</quote></supplied></p>
<p>*sari<!-- the unreduplicated form is not recorded in OJED --> masiha sirān ṅiṅət-iṅəta <app><lem type="norm">makasādhanaṅ</lem><rdg wit="#L">makasa:danaṁ</rdg><rdg wit="#K">makasḍanaṁ</rdg></app> vara-varah saṅ hyaṅ āgama <app><lem wit="#K">mānavādi</lem><rdg wit="#L">manava:vī</rdg></app>,
mvaṅ sakinapagəhaknikaṅ sapañjiṅ deśanya, <app><lem wit="#K">deśa ṅaranya,</lem><rdg wit="#L"/></app>
sadaṅayan<supplied reason="omitted">,</supplied> sajamus vuṅkal, savuravan, sakanuruhan,
an hana *kaparǝkanya deniṅ āgama, ya hika deśadr̥ṣṭa ṅaranya,
<!-- AG+TL have reached here on 2020-05-06 -->
<app><lem type="conj" rend="check">aṅkǝn</lem><rdg wit="#L #K">hankan</rdg></app><!-- maybe anǝka[kǝ]n> 'to cause to come (to), cause to reach, give, send, communicate'
atĕkĕn, atĕkĕn-tĕkĕn: 'to use a stick; to have as support, lean on' --> deśa sasiki svadeśanikaṅ vyavahāra, <term><app><lem type="emn">aṣṭādaśasu mārgeṣu</lem><rdg wit="#L">Aṣṭadaṣasu margge</rdg><rdg wit="#K">haṣṭa:deṣa:su ma:rgge</rdg></app></term>, irikā sthānaniṅ vyavahāra <app><lem wit="#L">vvalu</lem><rdg wit="#K">valu</rdg></app> vlas
kvehnya, <app><lem wit="#L">salviraniṅ vicāraniṅ</lem><rdg wit="#K">salviriṅ</rdg></app> vyavahāra, hana tinmunya ṅkāna salah siki,
<app><lem wit="#L">paḍa madudva-dudvan</lem><rdg wit="#K">padudvadudvan</rdg></app> viṣayanya.</p></div>
			<!--
L:		[01-14] Iṅsī ya kurute kaścit∙, hana vvaṁ mama:tyani nirdoṣa, kunaṁ deya[01-15]m va na prayaścati, tan paveḥ hirikaṁ yogya vehakna, Aveh irikaṁ [01-16] tan∙ yogya vehaknanya kunaṁ,
			stha:ne te dve viva:dasya, ya Ika: [01-17] stha:naniṁ vyava:hara, rvaṁ siki malanya, bhine ṣṭedaśada: punaḥ, matmahan ta [01-18] ya vva:luvla:s∙ vkasan∙ ||
K:			I§[SH]ṅsa: ya kurute kaścit∙, hana: voṁ mamatyani nirdoṣa:, maṅlarani nirdoṣa, kunaṁ deyam va na prayaścati [2r2], tan paveḥ hirikaṁ yogya vehikna, Aveh irikaṁ tan∙ yogya vehaknanya kunaṁ,
			svane te [SH] dve vivadasya, ya hikaṁ sthananiṁ vyavahara, rvaṁ siki mulanya, bhine ṣṭedaśada punaḥ, matmahan ta ya valuvlas∙ vka[2r3]san∙ ||
			-->
			<div n="4"><p><supplied reason="subaudible"><quote type="basetext" xml:lang="san-Latn" source="MDhŚ08.003_insertedafter_oOr"><!-- argr2axja: here we have a stanza that occurs in some witness of the basetext but has been rejected from the critical edition whose numbering we're following-->
			<lg met="anuṣṭubh">
				<l>hiṁsāṁ yaḥ kurute kaś cid deyaṁ vā na prayacchati |</l>
				<l>sthāne te dve vivādasya <app><lem source="Svayambhu"><!-- argr2axja: we are here trying to represent that the lemma from this stanza in the Svayambhu itself supports the reading bhinne as opposed to bhinno -->bhinne</lem><rdg source="#Mandlik1886_01">bhinno</rdg><note>Mandlik's reading is also supported by a manuscript collated in Olivelle 2005.</note></app> ’ṣṭādaśadhā punaḥ ||</l>
				</lg>
			</quote></supplied></p><p>
			<term xml:lang="san-Latn"><app><lem type="emn">hiṁsāṁ yaḥ</lem><rdg wit="#L">Iṅsīya</rdg><rdg wit="#K">Iṅsa:ya</rdg></app> kurute kaś cit</term>,
			hana vvaṅ mamātyani nirdoṣa, <app><lem wit="#K">maṅlarani nirdoṣa,</lem><rdg wit="#L"/></app>
			kunaṅ <term xml:lang="san-Latn">deyam <app><lem type="norm">vā</lem><rdg wit="#L #K">va</rdg></app> na <app><lem type="emn">prayacchati</lem><rdg wit="#L #K">prayaścati</rdg></app></term>,
			tan paveh irikaṅ yogya <app><lem wit="#L">vehakna</lem><rdg wit="#K">vehikna</rdg></app>, aveh irikaṅ tan yogya vehaknanya kunaṅ,
			<term xml:lang="san-Latn"><app><lem wit="#L">sthāne</lem><rdg wit="#K">svane</rdg></app> te dve vivādasya</term>,
			ya <app><lem wit="#L">ikā</lem><rdg wit="#K">hikaṁ</rdg></app> sthānaniṅ vyavahāra, rvaṅ siki <app><lem wit="#K">mūlanya</lem><rdg wit="#L">malanya</rdg></app>,
			<term xml:lang="san-Latn"><app><lem type="norm">bhinne</lem><rdg wit="#L #K">bhine</rdg></app> <app><lem type="emn">’ṣṭādaśadhā</lem><rdg wit="#L">ṣṭedaśada:</rdg><rdg wit="#K">ṣṭedaśada</rdg></app> punaḥ</term>,
			matmahan ta ya vvalu vlas vkasan.</p>
			</div>
